Ducor first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusCA/>

===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Ducor had a population of 616. The population density was {{convert|1,105.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Ducor was 123 (20.0%) [[White Americans|White]], 1 (0.2%) [[African Americans|African American]], 7 (1.1%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 12 (1.9%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 358 (58.1%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 115 (18.7%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 558 persons (90.6%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Ducor CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0620032 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 19, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 151 households, out of which 86 (57.0%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 84 (55.6%) were married-couple households, 10 (6.6%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 27 (17.9%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 30 (19.9%) had a male householder with no partner present. 16 households (10.6%) were one person, and 8 (5.3%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 4.08.<ref name=DP1/> There were 128 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (84.8% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Ducor CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0620032 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 19, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 208 people (33.8%) under the age of 18, 70 people (11.4%) aged 18 to 24, 157 people (25.5%) aged 25 to 44, 115 people (18.7%) aged 45 to 64, and 66 people (10.7%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 28.1{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 94.9 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 151 housing units at an average density of {{convert|271.1|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, which were all occupied, 99 (65.6%) by homeowners and 52 (34.4%) by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0620032|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715024523/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0620032|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Ducor CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that Ducor had a population of 612. The population density was {{convert|1,002.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Ducor was 251 (41.0%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 15 (2.5%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 20 (3.3%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 302 (49.3%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 24 (3.9%) from two or more races.  [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 502 persons (82.0%).

The Census reported that 612 people (100% of the population) lived in households, 0 (0%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 142 households, out of which 89 (62.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 103 (72.5%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 13 (9.2%) had a female householder with no husband present, 16 (11.3%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 12 (8.5%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 1 (0.7%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 6 households (4.2%) were made up of individuals, and 1 (0.7%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 4.31.  There were 132 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (93.0% of all households); the average family size was 4.40.

The population was spread out, with 200 people (32.7%) under the age of 18, 90 people (14.7%) aged 18 to 24, 135 people (22.1%) aged 25 to 44, 136 people (22.2%) aged 45 to 64, and 51 people (8.3%) who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 27.6 years. For every 100 females, there were 104.0 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 113.5 males.

There were 154 housing units at an average density of {{convert|252.4|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}, of which 105 (73.9%) were owner-occupied, and 37 (26.1%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0.9%; the rental vacancy rate was 11.9%.  434 people (70.9% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 178 people (29.1%) lived in rental housing units.

